Universal Editable Blocks + Versioning (Foundation)

Goal: every UI box becomes an editable, versioned “Block”, with safe locking + audit trail. This powers inline edits, AI edits, chat edits later.

1) Core Entities You Must Add (Minimum)

blocks (the box itself)

block_revisions (every change, human or AI)

block_links (connect blocks to proposal/roi/solution/etc.)

block_locks (prevent edits when sent/signed)

That’s it.

2) Block Types (Locked Enum)

Use a strict enum so UI renders consistently:

proposal_executive_brief

proposal_diagnosis

proposal_solution

proposal_timeline

proposal_team

proposal_governance

proposal_next_step

roi_summary_narrative

roi_financial_snapshot (numbers are referenced, not rewritten)

recommendation_card

contract_clause (usually locked)

followup_email_template

crm_note

3) blocks Schema (Source of Truth)
{
  "block_id": "B-000123",
  "block_type": "proposal_solution",
  "title": "Workflow Automation Layer",
  "content_format": "rich_text | structured_json",
  "content": {},
  "status": "draft | approved | locked",
  "source": "human | ai | mixed",
  "owner_user_id": "U-01",
  "created_at": "ISO_DATE",
  "updated_at": "ISO_DATE",
  "current_revision_id": "R-000900",
  "version": 1
}

Rules:

UI always renders from blocks.content of current_revision_id.

version increments only when a revision is accepted.

4) block_revisions Schema (Audit Trail)
{
  "revision_id": "R-000900",
  "block_id": "B-000123",
  "change_type": "create | edit | ai_improve | ai_expand | ai_simplify | chat_patch",
  "proposed_content": {},
  "diff_summary": "Short text summary of what changed",
  "created_by": "U-01",
  "created_by_type": "human | ai",
  "created_at": "ISO_DATE",
  "approval_status": "pending | accepted | rejected",
  "approved_by": null,
  "approved_at": null
}

Rules:

Revisions are never overwritten.

Only one pending revision allowed per block (simplifies UX).

Accepting revision updates the block’s content + current_revision_id.

5) block_links Schema (Connect Blocks to the System)

This lets one block attach to Proposal, Solution, ROI, Contract, etc.

{
  "link_id": "L-001",
  "block_id": "B-000123",
  "entity_type": "proposal | diagnosis | solution | phase | roi | contract | deal",
  "entity_id": "P-0001",
  "created_at": "ISO_DATE"
}

Rules:

A block can have multiple links (ex: solution block linked to proposal + solution_id).

This is how chat can “update all solution blocks”.

6) block_locks Schema (Non-Negotiable)
{
  "lock_id": "K-0001",
  "block_id": "B-000123",
  "lock_reason": "proposal_sent | contract_sent | contract_signed | compliance_locked | roi_locked",
  "locked_by": "system | admin",
  "locked_at": "ISO_DATE",
  "unlock_allowed": false
}

Rules:

If a block is locked, only admin can create revisions.

Contract clauses default unlock_allowed=false.

7) Editing UX Rules (So it stays clean)

Each block shows:

Title

Status badge (Draft/Approved/Locked)

“Edit” button (if not locked)

“History” button

If pending revision exists: “Review changes” (Accept / Reject)

No silent edits. Ever.

8) Proposal “Ready Gate” now uses Blocks

Proposal can move forward only if required blocks exist and are approved:

Required block set for Proposal readiness:

proposal_executive_brief (approved)

3× proposal_diagnosis (approved)

2× proposal_solution (approved)

proposal_next_step (approved)

Later phases add timeline/team/governance requirements.

9) ROI Protection Rule (Important)

roi_financial_snapshot is a reference block:

It pulls numbers from ROI engine outputs

Humans/AI can only edit the narrative block (roi_summary_narrative)

Not the numbers

This avoids “editing ROI”.